|CKBStreet Samurai Resources|000

|CKBEdge|000
|CK0Edge represents positioning, telemetry, and openings created during a
fight. It is a temporary combat resource, not experience. The monitor,
samstatus, and dashboard always show the current amount and live maximum. An
installed Second Spur can expand that maximum.|000

|CK0Snap Cut produces Edge whenever it deals damage. A Threat Scan lock lets a
damaging Ripcut pierce armour, deal additional damage, consume the lock, and
produce Edge. Jolt can produce Edge while the Cortex is already under elevated
thermal load. A damaging Photon Lance or Micro-Missile Swarm salvo also produces
Edge. The Ronin-sama Kernel can establish Edge when a new attacker enters its
telemetry.|000

|CK0Most active routines automatically route one available Edge as an optional
bonus. That bonus improves what the routine already does: damage, duration,
shielding, healing, or control strength. The shell reports an EDGE ROUTE when
this happens. No ordinary routine requires Edge to perform its base effect.|000

|CK0Smart Smoke routes Edge into one additional point of personal cover and a
longer deployment. Jammer Field routes Edge into stronger hostile-output
suppression, a faster attack-desynchronization pulse, and additional duration.
These bonuses remain distinct: Smoke protects its operator, while Jammer
degrades hostiles fighting the operator's nearby team.|000

|CK0Ghoststep repositions without Edge, keeps the primary engagement, sheds
secondary pressure, and arms a short-lived avoidance frame. Its follow-up can
route up to two Edge into the primary target; the full two-Edge route makes the
cut armour-piercing. Zero Signal uses available Edge differently: one routed
Edge extends concealment and adds another blocked combat reacquisition attempt.
Armor Weave creates Edge when its shielding is fully depleted. Predictive Sight
commits Edge only when it actually prevents damage and can refund it on a
particularly strong response.|000

|CK0A deployed Monowire produces Edge on its first confirmed cut against each
opponent. The command monowire edge deliberately spends Edge to arm the next
confirmed hit as an armour-piercing breach; it never spends Edge without that
command. Chrome Tempest works with an empty pool and converts any accumulated
Edge into a stronger finishing sequence. Tempest stabilize still reserves one
Edge specifically to avoid thermal lockout.|000

|CKBHeat|000
|CK0Heat is the Cortex's live thermal load. The monitor labels the current band
as CLEAN, REDLINE, OVERHEAT, or LOCKOUT. Some offensive routines become more
effective outside the clean band, but reaching the current thermal ceiling
causes thermal lockout. While locked, routines that would create Heat cannot
start until the system cools far enough to authenticate them again.|000

|CKBRedline and lockout|000

|CK0Most active routines add Heat only after they produce their intended
effect. Rejected commands, missing targets, and failed validation do not create
thermal load. Active routines have no individual cooldowns; they use a short,
shared Cortex execution cycle alongside Darkwind's normal action pacing.|000

|CK0Heat clears automatically over time and cools faster outside combat.
Overclock does not add Heat; it temporarily raises the thermal ceiling while
placing wear on the Cortex OS. Cold Signal reduces some incoming thermal
bursts, and Overdrive can absorb the opening burst of an engagement. These
systems provide headroom but do not make Heat irrelevant.|000

|CK0At Guild Level 11, "thermalpurge vent" provides an emergency escape from
accumulated Heat and thermal lockout. It clears the entire thermal load at once,
but the forced backwash causes severe integrity wear to both the Cortex OS and
Thermal Exchange Manifold. It is an emergency trade, not routine cooling.|000

|CK0Armor Weave and Monowire report their applied thermal load when used.
Armor Weave's Heat follows the shield charge it creates and its collapse adds
another burst when the shielding is fully consumed. Chrome Tempest normally
drives the Cortex to lockout; tempest stabilize uses the sequence's reserved
Edge to stop just short of that shutdown.|000

|CKBReading the system|000
|CK0Use samstatus for a compact resource and cycle report, dashboard for full
hardware diagnostics, and samhelp mon for the combat-monitor legend. If a
routine says the system is thermally locked, stop issuing Heat-producing
firmware and allow the live Heat value to fall.|000
